1015:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_SensingCSD_LL.c **** *
1016:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_SensingCSD_LL.c **** * \brief
1017:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_SensingCSD_LL.c **** *  Performs extended initialization for the CSD widget and also performs
1018:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_SensingCSD_LL.c **** *  initialization required for a specific sensor in the widget. This function
1019:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_SensingCSD_LL.c **** *  requires using the CapSense_1_CSDScanExt() function to initiate a scan.
1020:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_SensingCSD_LL.c **** *
1021:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_SensingCSD_LL.c **** * \details
1022:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_SensingCSD_LL.c **** *  This function does the same as CapSense_1_CSDSetupWidget() and also
1023:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_SensingCSD_LL.c **** *  does the following tasks:
1024:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_SensingCSD_LL.c **** *    1. Connects the first sensor of the widget.
1025:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_SensingCSD_LL.c **** *    2. Configures the IDAC value.
1026:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_SensingCSD_LL.c **** *    3. Initializes an interrupt callback function to initialize a scan of the
1027:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_SensingCSD_LL.c **** *  next sensors in a widget.
1028:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_SensingCSD_LL.c **** *
1029:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_SensingCSD_LL.c **** *  Once this function is called to initialize a widget and a sensor, the
1030:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_SensingCSD_LL.c **** *  CapSense_1_CSDScanExt() function is called to scan the sensor.
1031:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_SensingCSD_LL.c **** *
1032:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_SensingCSD_LL.c **** *  This function is called when no scanning is in progress. I.e.
1033:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_SensingCSD_LL.c **** *  CapSense_1_IsBusy() returns a non-busy status.
1034:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_SensingCSD_LL.c **** *
1035:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_SensingCSD_LL.c **** *  Calling this function directly from the application layer is not
1036:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_SensingCSD_LL.c **** *  recommended. This function is used to implement only the user's specific
1037:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_SensingCSD_LL.c **** *  use cases (for faster execution time or pipeline scanning for example).
1038:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_SensingCSD_LL.c **** *
1039:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_SensingCSD_LL.c **** * \param widgetId
1040:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_SensingCSD_LL.c **** *  Specifies the ID number of the widget to perform hardware and firmware
1041:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_SensingCSD_LL.c **** *  initialization required for scanning the specific sensor in the specific
1042:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_SensingCSD_LL.c **** *  widget.
1043:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_SensingCSD_LL.c **** *  A macro for the widget ID can be found in the CapSense_1 Configuration header
1044:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_SensingCSD_LL.c **** *  file defined as CapSense_1_<WidgetName>_WDGT_ID.
1045:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_SensingCSD_LL.c **** *
1046:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_SensingCSD_LL.c **** * \param sensorId
1047:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_SensingCSD_LL.c **** *  Specifies the ID number of the sensor within the widget to perform hardware
